#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:123
msgid "``@param``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:123
msgid ""
"Documents a parameter just like in Doxygen (must be followed by parameter "
"name)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:123
msgid "function, event, enum values, error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:124
msgid "``@return``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:124
msgid "Documents the return variables of a contract's function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:124 ../../../natspec-format.rst:125
msgid "function, enum, enum values, public state variable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:125
msgid "``@inheritdoc``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:125
msgid ""
"Copies all missing tags from the base function (must be followed by the "
"contract name)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:126
msgid "``@custom:...``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:126
msgid "Custom tag, semantics is application-defined"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:126
msgid "everywhere"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:129
msgid ""
"If your function returns multiple values, like ``(int quotient, int "
"remainder)`` then use multiple ``@return`` statements in the same format as "
"the ``@param`` statements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:132
msgid ""
"Custom tags start with ``@custom:`` and must be followed by one or more "
"lowercase letters or hyphens. It cannot start with a hyphen however. They "
"can be used everywhere and are part of the developer documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:138
msgid "Dynamic expressions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:140
msgid ""
"The Solidity compiler will pass through NatSpec documentation from your "
"Solidity source code to the JSON output as described in this guide. The "
"consumer of this JSON output, for example the end-user client software, may "
"present this to the end-user directly or it may apply some pre-processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:144
msgid "For example, some client software will render:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:146
msgid "/// @notice This function will multiply `a` by 7"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:150
msgid "to the end-user as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:152
msgid "This function will multiply 10 by 7"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:156
msgid ""
"if a function is being called and the input ``a`` is assigned a value of 10."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:161
msgid "Inheritance Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:163
msgid ""
"Functions without NatSpec will automatically inherit the documentation of "
"their base function. Exceptions to this are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:166
msgid "When the parameter names are different."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:167
msgid "When there is more than one base function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:168
msgid ""
"When there is an explicit ``@inheritdoc`` tag which specifies which contract "
"should be used to inherit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:173
msgid "Documentation Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:175
msgid ""
"When parsed by the compiler, documentation such as the one from the above "
"example will produce two different JSON files. One is meant to be consumed "
"by the end user as a notice when a function is executed and the other to be "
"used by the developer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:180
msgid ""
"If the above contract is saved as ``ex1.sol`` then you can generate the "
"documentation using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:183
msgid "solc --userdoc --devdoc ex1.sol"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:187
msgid "And the output is below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:190
msgid ""
"Starting Solidity version 0.6.11 the NatSpec output also contains a "
"``version`` and a ``kind`` field. Currently the ``version`` is set to ``1`` "
"and ``kind`` must be one of ``user`` or ``dev``. In the future it is "
"possible that new versions will be introduced, deprecating older ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:197
msgid "User Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:199
msgid ""
"The above documentation will produce the following user documentation JSON "
"file as output for the ``Tree`` contract:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:202
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\" : 1,\n"
"  \"kind\" : \"user\",\n"
"  \"methods\" :\n"
"  {\n"
"    \"age(uint256)\" :\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"notice\" : \"Calculate tree age in years, rounded up, for live "
"trees\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"leaves()\" :\n"
"    {\n"
"        \"notice\" : \"Returns the amount of leaves the tree has.\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  },\n"
"  \"notice\" : \"You can use this contract for only the most basic "
"simulation\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../natspec-format.rst:221
msgid ""
"Note that the key by which to find the methods is the function's canonical "
"signature as defined in the :ref:`Contract ABI <abi_function_selector>` and "
"not simply the function's name."
msgstr ""

